channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Police enter encampment at UCLA as protests disrupt colleges across the US
item.description: Police are cracking down on protests against Israel's bombardment of Gaza at campuses across the US. Follow for live updates.

item.title: 6 people, including 3-year-old, shot at Fort Worth apartment complex
item.description: At least six people ranging between the ages of 3 to 19-years-old have been shot at an apartment complex in Fort Worth, Texas, police say.

item.title: May 1, 2024 - US campus protests
item.description: Police are cracking down on protests against Israel's bombardment of Gaza at campuses across the US.

item.title: 'Violent protest is not protected,' Biden says of college campus unrest
item.description: President Joe Biden on Thursday spoke from the White House on college protests happening across the nation in connection with the Israel-Hamas war.

item.title: Former lawyer for Stormy Daniels testifies in Trump hush money trial
item.description: Former President Donald Trump's hush money trial continues in New York. Follow here for the latest live news updates, analysis and more.

item.title: More than 16K pounds of ground beef recalled for potential E. coli contamination
item.description: Cargill Meat Solutions recalled over 16,000 pounds of raw ground beef that was sold in 9 states at Walmart stores.

item.title: Fed holds interest rates at 23-year high as inflation continues to push back timing of a rate cut
item.description: The Federal Reserve said Wednesday it will hold interest rates at a 23-year high, making borrowing tougher for everything from car loans to mortgages.

item.title: Dan Schneider sues 'Quiet on Set' producers for defamation, calls series a 'hit job'
item.description: Dan Schneider files a defamation lawsuit against the producers of "Quiet on Set" docuseries.

item.title: April 30, 2024 - US university protests
item.description: Over 100 demonstrators were arrested at Columbia University and City College of New York after police cracked down on people protesting Israel's war in Gaza.

item.title: Authorities arrest suspect in killing of Chicago Police Officer Luis Huesca
item.description: The Chicago Police Department and the U.S. Marshals have taken Xavier L. Tate Jr. into custody on suspicion of murder.
